# Project Configuration for Elixir Phoenix Skills

This template helps you configure your Elixir/Phoenix project to work with the skills in this repository.

## Installation

Add the skills to your project:

```bash
# Install all skills
npx skills add igmarin/elixir-phoenix-skills

# Or install specific skills
npx skills add igmarin/elixir-phoenix-skills/skills/elixir-essentials
npx skills add igmarin/elixir-phoenix-skills/skills/phoenix-liveview-essentials
npx skills add igmarin/elixir-phoenix-skills/skills/ecto-essentials
```

## Project Setup

### 1. Configure your mix.exs

Ensure your project has the necessary dependencies:

```elixir
defp deps do
  [
    # Core Phoenix
    {:phoenix, "~> 1.7"},
    {:phoenix_live_view, "~> 0.20"},
    {:ecto_sql, "~> 3.11"},
    
    # Code quality
    {:credo, "~> 1.7", only: [:dev, :test], runtime: false},
    {:dialyxir, "~> 1.4", only: [:dev, :test], runtime: false},
    
    # Testing
    {:stream_data, "~> 1.0", only: :test},
    
    # Background jobs (if using Oban)
    {:oban, "~> 2.17"},
    
    # HTTP client
    {:req, "~> 0.5"},
    
    # Email
    {:swoosh, "~> 1.14"},
    
    # Caching
    {:cachex, "~> 3.6"},
    
    # Internationalization
    {:gettext, "~> 0.26"}
  ]
end
```

### 2. Configure .formatter.exs

```elixir
[
  import_deps: [:ecto, :ecto_sql, :phoenix],
  subdirectories: ["priv/*/migrations"],
  plugins: [Phoenix.LiveView.HTMLFormatter],
  inputs: ["*.{heex,ex,exs}", "{config,lib,test}/**/*.{heex,ex,exs}", "priv/*/seeds.exs"]
]
```

### 3. Configure .credo.exs

Use the `credo-config` skill to set up Credo for your project.

### 4. Configure .dialyzer_ignore.exs

Use the `typespec-dialyzer` skill to set up Dialyzer for your project.

