## Development Workflow

### 1. Start with Context

Before writing code, use the appropriate skill:

```
# For new LiveView
Use phoenix-liveview-essentials skill

# For new database operation
Use ecto-essentials skill

# For new background job
Use oban-essentials skill
```

### 2. Write Tests First

Always use the testing-essentials skill:

```
# TDD workflow
1. Write failing test
2. Implement to make it pass
3. Refactor
4. Repeat
```

### 3. Apply Quality Checks

Before committing:

```bash
# Format code
mix format

# Run Credo
mix credo

# Run Dialyzer
mix dialyzer

# Run tests
mix test
```

### 4. Review with Security in Mind

Use the security-essentials skill to review:

- Input validation
- SQL injection prevention
- XSS prevention
- CSRF protection
- Secure password handling

## Project Structure

Follow the standard Phoenix project structure:

```
my_app/
├── lib/
│   ├── my_app/              # Business logic
│   │   ├── accounts/        # Context modules
│   │   ├── blog/
│   │   └── repo.ex
│   └── my_app_web/          # Web layer
│       ├── live/            # LiveView modules
│       ├── controllers/     # Controllers
│       ├── components/      # Function components
│       └── router.ex
├── test/                    # Tests
├── priv/
│   ├── repo/migrations/     # Database migrations
│   └── gettext/             # Translations
└── config/                  # Configuration
```

## Common Patterns

### Context Module Pattern

```elixir
defmodule MyApp.Blog do
  @moduledoc """
  The Blog context.
  """

  import Ecto.Query, warn: false
  alias MyApp.Repo

  alias MyApp.Blog.Post

  @doc """
  Returns the list of posts.
  """
  def list_posts do
    Repo.all(Post)
  end

  @doc """
  Gets a single post.
  """
  def get_post!(id), do: Repo.get!(Post, id)

  @doc """
  Creates a post.
  """
  def create_post(attrs \\ %{}) do
    %Post{}
    |> Post.changeset(attrs)
    |> Repo.insert()
  end
end
```

### LiveView Pattern

```elixir
defmodule MyAppWeb.PostLive.Index do
  use MyAppWeb, :live_view

  alias MyApp.Blog

  @impl true
  def mount(_params, _session, socket) do
    {:ok, stream(socket, :posts, Blog.list_posts())}
  end

  @impl true
  def handle_event("delete", %{"id" => id}, socket) do
    post = Blog.get_post!(id)
    {:ok, _} = Blog.delete_post(post)

    {:noreply, stream_delete(socket, :posts, post)}
  end
end
```

### Testing Pattern

```elixir
defmodule MyApp.BlogTest do
  use MyApp.DataCase, async: true

  alias MyApp.Blog

  describe "posts" do
    test "list_posts/0 returns all posts" do
      post = post_fixture()
      assert Blog.list_posts() == [post]
    end

    test "create_post/1 with valid data creates a post" do
      attrs = %{title: "Test Post", body: "Test body"}
      assert {:ok, %Post{} = post} = Blog.create_post(attrs)
      assert post.title == "Test Post"
    end
  end
end
```

